.\" playfield-compiler.1.mdoc - Playfield compiler manpage
.Dd September 2025
.Dt PLAYFIELD-COMPILER 1
.Os Playfield 1.0
.Sh NAME
.Nm playfield-compiler
.Nd compile Playfield scripts into bytecode
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar sourcefiles ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
translates Playfield script files
.Pa .pf
into bytecode files with the extension
.Pa .pfc .
.Pp
Each input file is compiled independently.
The output file has the same basename as the input,
with its extension replaced by
.Pa .pfc .
For example, compiling
.Pa sample.pf
produces
.Pa sample.pfc
in the same directory.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Compile a single script:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
playfield-compiler sample.pf
.Ed
.Pp
Compile multiple scripts:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
playfield-compiler main.pf enemy.pf level.pf
.Ed
.Pp
The above command produces:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
main.pfc enemy.pfc level.pfc
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr playfield 1 ,
.Xr playfield-pack 1
